The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal coefficients in Compute-and-Forward (C&F) for distributed antenna systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses lattice-based algorithms, which are commonly used in network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes low complexity algorithms, which are relevant to the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM) where efficient algorithms are important for processing large amounts of data.
